# Testes de Hooks React Native

## renderHook Basico

```tsx
import { renderHook, act, waitFor } from "@testing-library/react-native";
import { usePersistedState } from "./usePersistedState";

describe("usePersistedState", () => {
  it("retorna valor padrao inicialmente", () => {
    const { result } = renderHook(() => usePersistedState("key", "default"));
    expect(result.current.value).toBe("default");
    expect(result.current.loading).toBe(true);
  });

  it("atualiza valor e persiste", async () => {
    const { result } = renderHook(() => usePersistedState("key", "default"));
    await act(async () => {
      await result.current.update("novo");
    });
    expect(result.current.value).toBe("novo");
  });
});
```

## Mock de Navegacao

```tsx
const mockNavigate = jest.fn();
const mockGoBack = jest.fn();
const mockParams = { userId: "123" };

jest.mock("@react-navigation/native", () => ({
  useNavigation: () => ({ navigate: mockNavigate, goBack: mockGoBack }),
  useRoute: () => ({ params: mockParams }),
  useFocusEffect: jest.fn((cb) => cb()),
}));

describe("useProfileScreen", () => {
  beforeEach(() => jest.clearAllMocks());

  it("retorna userId dos params", () => {
    const { result } = renderHook(() => useProfileScreen());
    expect(result.current.userId).toBe("123");
  });

  it("navega para edicao", () => {
    const { result } = renderHook(() => useProfileScreen());
    act(() => result.current.goToEdit());
    expect(mockNavigate).toHaveBeenCalledWith("EditProfile", { userId: "123" });
  });
});
```

## Mock de AsyncStorage

```tsx
jest.mock("@react-native-async-storage/async-storage", () => ({
  getItem: jest.fn(() => Promise.resolve(null)),
  setItem: jest.fn(() => Promise.resolve()),
  removeItem: jest.fn(() => Promise.resolve()),
}));
```

## Convencoes

- `renderHook` para testar hooks isoladamente
- `act` para atualizacoes de estado sincronas
- `waitFor` para efeitos assincronos
- Mocks de navegacao no topo do arquivo
- `beforeEach(() => jest.clearAllMocks())` para isolamento
